Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_gates(25.10)                                        report_gates(25.10)

Name
       report_gates  -  Reports  the technology library cells that were imple-
       mented (and identifies their originating libraries), the  area  of  the
       cell  instances,  and the break up of the instances into timing models,
       sequential cells, integrated clock-gating  cells,  inverters,  buffers,
       and logic gate cells

Syntax
       report_gates

       [-help]

       [-hinst <hInstName>]

       [-out_file <fileName>]

       [-sort   {name  count  area  leakage_power  internal_power  total_power
       switching_power}] [-power | -leakage_power ]

       Reports the technology library cells that were implemented (and identi-
       fies their originating libraries), the area of the cell instances,  and
       the break up of the instances into timing models, sequential cells, in-
       tegrated  clock-gating cells, inverters, buffers, and logic gate cells.
       Optionally power information can be reported.

       The result is based on the cell_area calculated from  LIB  information.
       Use  set_db use_area_from_lef true (default: false), if you want to get
       correlation between reports generated with report_gates command and re-
       port_qor or report_utilization commands. When a lef is read into Genus,
       the property "use_area_from_lef" is automatically set to true.

       Timing models can refer to memory cells, IPs, and so on.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each report_gates parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_gates

       -hinst <hInstName>
              Specifies the name of the hinst to collect the cell information.
              Only cells in the specified hinst will be considered.

       -leakage_power
              Provides leakage power statistic only.

       -out_file <fileName>
              Specifies  the file in which report will be saved. If not speci-
              fied, information is dumped in the log.

       -power Provides internal, switching, leakage and total power statistic.

       -sort {name count area leakage_power internal_power total_power switch-
       ing_power}
              Specifies the sorting criteria to sort content of the tables  to
              generate  leakage_power/internal_power  value  only respected if
              the option -power is also specified.

Examples
       >report_gates -sort name -out_file check.rpt

